able map view with an interface similar to the one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"provided by Apple’s MapKit.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMapView"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolyline","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the line segments that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"path along which something moves."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolyline"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNMultiPolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolyline"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","isActive":true},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disconnected vertices, specified as ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"title":"MLNPointCollection","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPointCollection"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapView/addAnnotation:":{"role":"symbol","title":"addAnnotation:","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds an annotation to the map view."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addAnnotation:"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/addannotation:","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}]}}}